modules.description: This module defines predefined font sizes for use in image generation tasks. It provides constants representing different font scales, such as tiny, small, medium, large, and giant. These font values are used directly when drawing text onto images with associated graphics libraries.

This module handles image creation, manipulation, and text rendering using the GD library. It supports operations like creating truecolor images, opening PNG and JPEG files, and drawing text with TrueType fonts, including configurable spacing and character maps. Concrete use cases include generating dynamic images with overlaid text, such as charts, banners, or watermarked photos.
